The older brother showed me really odd grappling "handles," like diggin' your fingertips up under the jawbone (and THAT SHIT HURTS), clavicles, up under the lower rib cage.. anyplace you can dig in for purchase to wrench an opponent off balance. Years later, I got to use a jaw handle once to get out of a mount and it worked great! But I don't see stuff like that in MMA/UFC. Was my neighbors instructor a weirdo?
